## 🚀 5-Week Build Sequence

### Week 1: Infrastructure & Pipeline Skeleton
> [cite_start]**Goal**: Trigger the webhook and get a rough MP4 back[cite: 19, 46].
* [cite_start]**Days 1–2**: Create accounts (Render, B2, n8n, Anthropic, Replicate, ElevenLabs)[cite: 21]. [cite_start]Buy a .in or .co domain[cite: 22].
  - **Render Infrastructure Setup**:
    - Deploy PostgreSQL database (Starter plan)
    - Deploy Redis instance for job queue
    - Deploy Background Worker with FFmpeg
    - Apply $500 credits and set billing alert at $400
  - **Database Setup**: Run the PostgreSQL schema (see Database Schema section)
  - **Monitoring**: Set up Sentry (free tier) and BetterStack (₹800/mo)
* [cite_start]**Days 3–4**: Build the n8n sequence (Webhook → Anthropic → Loop Scenes → Replicate → ElevenLabs → Render Worker/FFmpeg → Backblaze B2) [cite: 28-36].
  - Integrate Redis job queue between n8n and Render Worker
  - Add PostgreSQL logging for each video job (status, timestamps, costs)
* [cite_start]**Days 5–6**: Test with 5 real estate topics[cite: 38].
  - **Performance Testing**: Track generation time for each step:
    - **Target total time**: <5 minutes per video
    - Claude 3.5 Haiku script: <30 seconds
    - Replicate FLUX (5 images): <2 minutes
    - ElevenLabs voice: <20 seconds
    - FFmpeg assembly: <2 minutes
  - If total time >5 minutes, identify bottleneck and upgrade Render Worker to Standard ($25/mo)
  - [cite_start]Fix common JSON parsing and timeout errors[cite: 40, 41].
* [cite_start]**Day 7**: Setup Sentry error monitoring and a 6-hour cron health check in n8n [cite: 43-45].
  - Create simple admin dashboard (password-protected HTML page):
    - Jobs in queue (from Redis)
    - Failed jobs (from PostgreSQL)
    - Today's API costs
    - Total videos generated counter

### Week 2: Quality & Style Optimization
> [cite_start]**Goal**: Produce videos a real estate agent would actually post[cite: 48].
* [cite_start]**Prompts**: Create a style library for "cinematic interior photography" to avoid generic AI looks[cite: 52, 53].
* [cite_start]**Voice**: Use high-quality voices like 'Rachel' or 'Aria' with SSML pauses for human-like delivery[cite: 56, 57].
* [cite_start]**FFmpeg**: Add 0.4s crossfade dissolves and Ken Burns (slow zoom) effects[cite: 60, 61].
* [cite_start]**QA**: Manually review all videos for the first 30 days to ensure "gold standard" demo assets[cite: 65, 70].

### Week 3: Landing Page & Sales Outreach
> [cite_start]**Goal**: 10 paying customers (₹9,990 MRR)[cite: 72, 94].
* **Landing Page**: One page on Framer. Offer 20 videos for ₹999/month. [cite_start]Use a "free sample" Google Form as the CTA [cite: 73-79].
* [cite_start]**Outreach**: Send 50 DMs/day to real estate agents using a specific script offering a free sample Reel [cite: 84-86].
* **Customer Acquisition Cost (CAC) Tracking**:
  - Create a Google Sheet with columns: Date, DMs Sent, Samples Delivered, Paid Conversions, CAC
  - Formula: CAC = (Time spent × ₹500/hour + Ad spend) / Paid Conversions
  - **Target CAC**: <₹3,000 (break-even in first month with 78% margin)
  - Track daily metrics:
    - DM → Sample conversion rate (target: >10%)
    - Sample → Paid conversion rate (target: >20%)
  - If CAC >₹3,000 by day 5, pivot strategy:
    - Test different DM scripts
    - Add referral incentive (₹500 credit per referral)
    - Target brokerages instead of individual agents
* [cite_start]**Closing**: Use Razorpay links for immediate payment collection[cite: 92].

### Week 4: Automated Intake & Payments
> [cite_start]**Goal**: Remove yourself from the intake process[cite: 96].
* [cite_start]**Intake**: Replace Google Forms with a password-gated Typeform that triggers the n8n workflow [cite: 97-101].
* [cite_start]**Payments**: Set up Stripe subscriptions to automate access [cite: 103-105].
* [cite_start]**Auto-Retry**: Add logic to n8n to retry failed generations with simplified prompts if errors occur [cite: 107-109].

### Week 5: Feedback & Iteration
> [cite_start]**Goal**: Fix the top 3 complaints from your first 10 customers[cite: 113].
* [cite_start]Send WhatsApp voice notes to each customer to ask for feedback[cite: 114].
* [cite_start]Only build features requested by at least 3 people (e.g., captions, brand colors, or more styles)[cite: 117, 118].

